Preheat a baking sheet in the oven at 200C/400F/Gas 6.Place all the ingredients into the bowl of a food processor and blend until the ingredients have combined and formed a dough.Place the dough onto a floured surface and shape the dough, with floured hands, into a long ciabatta shape.Place the ciabatta onto the hot baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes, or until cooked through and golden-brown in colour. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for two minutes.Cut diagonally into thin slices to make the biscotti.To serve, place the biscotti into a clean bowl.